      "message": "Yes this is wacky.  It is to preserve Android\u0027s kNeverCopyPixels behavior.\n\nWhen Android calls drawBitmap(), we wrap it in an SkImage and draw.  In the case that we need a color xform, we wrap it in a SkCSXImage and draw.  In order to avoid repeating the upload+colorxform step every time we draw, we want the gen id on the image to always match the bitmap.\n\nThis requires a guarantee: when Android draws these pixels, they are always drawn with the same color space.\n\nThis complexity will go away when Android just uses SkImages.\n\n----------------\n\nMaybe I should just make this weird gen id hackery available from the private constructor?  Or I can remove it altogether from this CL, and we can consider it on its own with changes to the Android API.",
